HEADWORD: Fairway
<hw>Fair"way`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
navigable part of a river, bay, etc., through which vessels enter or
depart; the part of a harbor or channel ehich is kept open and
unobstructed for the passage of vessels.</def>
<rj><au>Totten.</au></rj></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(golf)</fld> <def>That part of a golf course between
the tee and the green which is of closely mowed grass, as contrasted to
the <contr>rough</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fair-weather</ent>⟦br⟧
